":\\\"Khalra Abducted and Murdered\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Taken by Punjab Police, tortured, killed, body disposed in Sutlej river.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"The Satluj Files: Censored, Released, Removed — The 48-Hour Life of India's Most Controversial Film\\\",\\\"sourceSlug\\\":\\\"/story/satluj-ban\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"story\\\"},{\\\"date\\\":\\\"1995-01-01\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Khalra Publishes Cremation Ground Findings\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Documents 2,000+ unclaimed bodies cremated at municipal grounds (1984-1994).\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"The Satluj Files: Censored, Released, Removed — The 48-Hour Life of India's Most Controversial Film\\\",\\\"sourceSlug\\\":\\\"/story/satluj-ban\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"story\\\"},{\\\"date\\\":\\\"1993-09-07\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Peace and Tranquility Agreement\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"India and China sign agreement to maintain peace along LAC pending final resolution of border dispute.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"India-China at the Crossroads: Four Years After Galwan, the Border Remains the Flashpoint\\\",\\\"sourceSlug\\\":\\\"/story/india-china-border-tensions\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"story\\\"},{\\\"date\\\":\\\"1991-01-01\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Look East Policy Launched\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"India launches Look East policy under PM Narasimha Rao to deepen economic and strategic ties with Southeast Asia.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"India's Foreign Policy at 80: From Non-Alignment to Multi-Alignment\\\",\\\"sourceSlug\\\":\\\"/story/indias-foreign-policy\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"story\\\"},{\\\"date\\\":\\\"1988-12-19\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Rajiv Gandhi Visit\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"PM Rajiv Gandhi's historic visit to Beijing breaks the post-war freeze. Joint Working Group on border dispute established.\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"India-China: Two Asian Giants in an Era of Mistrust and Strategic Rivalry\\\",\\\"sourceSlug\\\":\\\"/story/india-china-relations\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"story\\\"},{\\\"date\\\":\\\"19